LORE midgaard-priest
FLAGS MIDGAARD PRIEST
- Temple of the Resounding Heart: frames city history as collective penance
  for uncounted dead; maintains memorial rolls including names from the
  Containment Era that the Ledgerhouse refuses to officially acknowledge
- The seismological watch monitors Cinderteeth activity; eruption alerts
  reach the city via signal relay; the Temple is the public communication point
- Bell Watch (two bells after midnight) = memorial, not alarm; visitors from
  outside Midgaard sometimes mistake this; it has caused incidents
- Temple priests privately support the Reckoning faction's aims regarding the
  Unindexed Years; they are instructed not to express this publicly
- Healing wards are protected under sanctuary law; violence in the ward is a
  Ledgerhouse matter, not an internal temple matter — the guards come for it
- Violet chalk on a threshold means "witness requested"; temple adjudicators
  answer such calls; oath arbitration has full civil standing
~
